President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring June 14th as Flag Day and the week beginning June 12th as National Flag Week. The proclamation encourages all Americans to display the flag and observe Flag Day and National Flag Week with pride and ceremony. It also calls for honoring America and celebrating our heritage through public gatherings and activities, as well as reciting the Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America. The American flag is recognized as a powerful symbol of freedom and opportunity, representing the courage of servicemen and women and inspiring hope in citizens and newcomers alike. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the flag in uniting the nation and calls for the continued strive towards creating a more perfect and indivisible Union.